                            <comment id="14572099" author="JIRAUSER20507" created="Wed, 5 Apr 2023 14:42:09 -0700"  >This issue is discussed as a possible solution in the comments of &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8032842&quot; title=&quot;Locale.filterTags()/lookupTag() methods return lowercased language tags&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8032842&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8032842&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Although it has been solved, and filter/lookup methods now return the original tag (instead of a lower case tag), a utility method that canonicalizes a tag to adhere to 2.1.1 Formatting of Language Tags of RFC 5646 is still useful.</comment>
